-- Harmony Gold Shuts Phakisa Mine After Explosion Kills Three, Injures Two
-- Carli Lourens
-- 2010-06-25T07:26:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/harmony-gold-shuts-phakisa-mine-after-explosion-kills-three-injures-two.html

          
          
             Harmony Gold Mining Co. Ltd. said it
temporarily shut down its Phakisa Mine in South Africa’s Free
State province after an explosion that killed three workers and
injured another two.  
 The company may start investigating the cause of the “very
unusual” explosion tomorrow, Tom Smith, chief operating officer
for Johannesburg-based Harmony Gold’s South African region, said
in a telephone interview today.  
